# CSP Third-Party Scripts (ERP)

Applies when adding analytics, tag managers, payment widgets, chat, maps, or any external script to `apps/erp`.

**Authority:** `.cursor/skills/csp-third-party/SKILL.md` · `apps/erp/src/proxy.ts` · `apps/erp/src/lib/security/csp-allowlist.ts`

## Non-negotiable rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Nonce source | `getCspNonce()` from `@/lib/security/nonce.server` — never generate in components |
| Script tag | `next/script` in **Server Components** only — never raw `<script>` |
| Nonce prop | `<Script nonce={nonce} ... />` when `nonce` is non-null |
| CSP domains | Add explicit origins to `csp-allowlist.ts` in the **same PR** |
| Wildcards | Never `*`, never bare `https:`, never `'unsafe-inline'` in production `script-src` |
| Client state | Never store nonce in cookies, localStorage, sessionStorage, or React state |
| Client bundles | Never import `getCspNonce()` from `"use client"` files |

## Workflow (same PR)

1. Add vendor origin(s) to `apps/erp/src/lib/security/csp-allowlist.ts` with a short comment naming the integration.
2. In a Server Component layout/page:

```tsx
import Script from "next/script";
import { getCspNonce } from "@/lib/security/nonce.server";

export default async function Layout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const nonce = await getCspNonce();

  return (
    <>
      {children}
      {nonce === null ? null : (
        <Script
          nonce={nonce}
          src="https://www.example-cdn.com/vendor.js"
          strategy="afterInteractive"
        />
      )}
    </>
  );
}
```

3. Map required directives (`script-src`, `connect-src`, `img-src`, `frame-src`) in the allowlist.
4. Run `pnpm check:csp-third-party` and `pnpm --filter @afenda/erp test:run`.

## Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// ❌ raw script
<script src="https://cdn.example.com/a.js" />

// ❌ Script without nonce
<Script src="https://cdn.example.com/a.js" />

// ❌ nonce generated in component
const nonce = crypto.randomUUID()

// ❌ client component importing server nonce helper
"use client";
import { getCspNonce } from "@/lib/security/nonce.server"

// ❌ inline snippet
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: "<script>...</script>" }} />
```

## Enforcement

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Skill | `.cursor/skills/csp-third-party/SKILL.md` |
| CI gate | `pnpm check:csp-third-party` |
| Cursor hook | `.cursor/hooks/guard-pre-tool-use.mjs` |
| Unit tests | `apps/erp/src/lib/security/__tests__/csp*.test.ts` |
